=Description=

"The For-Purpose Enterprise is a daring new approach to structuring your venture. It is not designed for business as usual. Through many years of implementing post-bureaucracy models such as Holacracy, proven methods have emerged to legally encode and support the global movement towards purpose-driven work and decentralized-organizations. 

It is time to evolve and encode the legal, financial, organizational, and social foundations of purpose-driven business. The For-Purpose Enterprise is a multi-stakeholder approach to legally encoding the dynamism of distributed-authority and the sustainability of shared risks and rewards."


=Characteristics=

"Financial models that facilitate the operational execution of dynamically and equitably accounting for shared risks and rewards.

Legal agreements that encode distributed-authority management and dynamic-equity profit sharing at the legal corporate level.

Social and cultural models of cohesion to integrate individual differences in the new world of inter-personal and operational complexity."


